<doc id="614103" wikidata="Q3174196" url="?curid=614103" title="Barleeia">
<text>Barleeia, or the barleysnails, is a genus of very small sea snails. They are marine gastropod micromollusks in the family Barleeiidae. These snails are usually only a couple of millimeters in length.

==Species==
Species within the genus &quot;Barleeia&quot; include:

* &quot;Barleeia aemilii&quot; Cape Verde
* &quot;Barleeia albicolor&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia alderi&quot; – West America
* &quot;Barleeia annamitica&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia bentleyi&quot; – West America
* &quot;Barleeia bifasciata&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia caffra&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia cala&quot; St. Helena
* &quot;Barleeia calcarea&quot; - Hawaii
* &quot;Barleeia californica&quot; - California barleysnail - America
* &quot;Barleeia carpenteri&quot; – West-America
* &quot;Barleeia chefiae&quot; Cape Verde
* &quot;Barleeia chrysomela&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia cinguloides&quot; Namibia, Angola.
* &quot;Barleeia congenita&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia coronadoensis&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia creutzbergi&quot; Mexico, Costa Rica, Cuba, Curaçao.
* &quot;Barleeia ephamilla&quot; St. Helena (&quot;taxon inquirendum&quot;)
* &quot;Barleeia fuscaexigua&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia fuscopicta&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia gougati&quot; Mediterranean
* &quot;Barleeia haliotiphila&quot; - abalone barleysnail - This intertidal snail is one of the most common gastropods to be found in the biotic community at moderate tidal levels. Its diet consists of algae, such as &quot;Rhodoglossum affine&quot;, &quot;Mastocarpus papillatus&quot;, &quot;Gigartina leptorhynchos&quot;. Range: East Pacific, North America.
* &quot;Barleeia juliae&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia lindae&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia malgascia&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia meridionalis&quot; Peru
* &quot;Barleeia mexicana&quot; Mexico, Cuba
* &quot;Barleeia microthyra&quot; Indo-Pacific
* &quot;Barleeia multicolor&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia oldroydi&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia orcutti&quot; West America
* &quot;Barleeia paupercula&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia pervulgata&quot; Namibia, Angola
* &quot;Barleeia picta&quot; Namibia, Angola
* &quot;Barleeia polychroma&quot; West America
* &quot;Barleeia procera&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia rubrooperculata&quot; southern Brazil, Uruguay.
* &quot;Barleeia sanjuanensis&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia seminulum&quot; Europe
* &quot;Barleeia simplex&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia smithi&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia subtenuis&quot; - Fragile barleysnail - America
* &quot;Barleeia taeniolata&quot; São Tomé and Príncipe
* &quot;Barleeia tincta&quot; - Caribbean barleysnail - eastern Florida, Trinidad.
* &quot;Barleeia tomensis&quot; São Tomé and Príncipe
* &quot;Barleeia translucens&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia trifasciata&quot; Japan
* &quot;Barleeia tropica&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia unifasciata&quot; - Shetland into Mediterranean; Canary Islands
* &quot;Barleeia verdensis&quot; Cape Verde

;Species brought into synonymy:
* &quot;Barleeia acuta&quot; - acute barleysnail - America: synonym of &quot;Pseudodiala acuta&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia angustata&quot; – Indo-Pacific: synonym of &quot;Ansola angustata&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia compacta&quot; (J. G. Jeffreys 1884) Europe: synonym of &quot;Barleeia gougeti&quot; (junior synonym)
* &quot;Barleeia rubra&quot; West Africa: synonym of &quot;Barleeia unifasciata&quot; 
* &quot;Barleeia zeteki&quot; West America: synonym of &quot;Barleeia paupercula&quot; 

==References==

* Ponder, W. F. (1967). The classification of the Rissoidae and Orbitestellidae with descriptions of some new taxa. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, Zoology. 9(17): 193–224, pls 1–13.

