<doc id="614124" wikidata="Q1757609" url="?curid=614124" title="Rivas, Nicaragua">
<text>Rivas () is a city and municipality in southwestern Nicaragua on the Isthmus of the same name. The city proper is the capital of the Department of Rivas and administrative centre for the surrounding municipality of the same name.

==Climate==
Rivas has a tropical savanna climate (Köppen climate classification &quot;Aw&quot;) with a short dry season from January to April and a lengthy wet season from May to October. Temperatures remain steady throughout the year with the dry season being slightly cooler and range from in January to in May. The average annual precipitation is .

==Notable people==
* Erasmo Ramírez, Major League Baseball pitcher.
* Violeta Chamorro, first female president of Nicaragua, was born in Rivas.

